Rules referring to fruit and vegetables in the EU, despite opposition from some states, have been softened on the grounds that the existing directive entails a waste of food.
The candidate to win the poll could be last year's EU prescription that inflatable balloons that are marketed are mandatory to warn that children under 8 are not allowed to inflate them without adult supervision.
The EU was referring here to an American study according to which, when talking about toys, balloons are the main cause of child death by suffocation.
A similar restriction on the use of mother-in-law by children up to the age of 14 is also in place.
Curious occurrences are born even in our country
