In the end, the European Commission was ready to help the Czech Republic and organised a public tender for the purchase of cereals from landlocked countries.
The grant to receive a grant was proposed to the municipalities by the ministry for local development led by Minister Pavel Němec (US-DEU). Specifically, it is intended for the drafting of grant applications from Brussels.
EU: Rare prescriptions are an exception
