Wentzler hopes to be able to resolve the issue favourably and commends the professionalism of the courts.
However, he also states that "the procedure is extremely expensive, both in terms of money and time."
It is difficult to estimate internal costs; The business archive has had to review files up to a hundred years old in order to provide evidence.
Five years ago Freudenberg offered the opposing side a "six-figure sum in euros" with the aim of reaching an amicable settlement, but was unsuccessful.
"This shows how much we care," Wentzler says.
The dangers lurking in the Far East threaten even to affect Europe.
specifically whether imitators secure rights to unprotected trademarks there.
