However, we are in the southernmost part of Azerbaijan; from here the border with Iran is only a few kilometers away.
Here live the "talyshi", a people of whom not much is known, apart from the fact that they perfectly master Persian and Azeri and that they are very long-lived.
Our final destination is Lerik.
This small town boasts perhaps too massive architecture designed in the Soviet era and that does not seem to fit at all in such a picturesque mountainous landscape.
