Personally, I have never been interested in power, but in situations as unjust as Ecuador's, that socioeconomic poverty can only be corrected from political power.
"My political movement believed that it was I who guaranteed that probable victory, because we have to accept that responsibility," he said.
If I win, it would be my last term in the presidency and from there we left public life.
If we lose the same.
"It's a decision," he said.
